From simple co-occurrence rules (Dagan and Itai 1990) through training decision trees to identify anaphor-antecedent pairs (Aone and Bennett 1995) to genetic algorithms to optimize the resolution factors (Or~san, Evans, and Mitkov 2000), the successful performance of more and more modern approaches was made possible by the availability of suitable corpora.
